RM  19114477
RT  Characterization of the Escherichia coli O157:H7 Sakai GadE regulon.
RA  Kailasan Vanaja S, Bergholz TM, Whittam TS;
RL  J Bacteriol. 2009;191:1868-1877.
CC  The decarboxylation of glutamate to 4-aminobutanoate, also known as
CC  gamma-aminobutyrate or GABA, coupled with glutamate-GABA antiport,
CC  provides a robust mechanism of glutamate-based acid resistance for
CC  Escherichia coli and other organisms that need to survive transient
CC  exposures to highly acidic pH. Import of the negatively charged
CC  glutamate, decarboxylation with the consumption of a proton, and export
CC  of the neutral molecule GABA serves to reduce cytosolic acidity.
CC  Similar cycles are driven by the decarboxylation of other amino acids.
**  NTL01BMA0910 represents a distinctive clade of probable antiporter,
**  next to the glutamate decarboxylase but also, usually near a
**  glutaminase (converts Gln to Glu plus NH3), so what antiports is a
**  question.
